						<summary>

						<p>Sculptured slab in the Āvulamāla, 1(1/2) miles to the west of the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Parīdhāvi, Māgha śu. 3.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records that Pālēṭi Buchchana, who was an artisan, carved the sculptures of 150 cows.</p>						

